This paper presents a logic for action theory, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The logic is a temporal logic, which is often studied in the subfield of logic and computation (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of quantifiers, which is a topic in programming languages and formal methods (cs.PL). The paper presents tableaux rules, which are a proof technique often used in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the decidable fragment of the logic, which is a topic in machine learning and theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
